text: Szentlőrinci Atlétikai Club is a Hungarian football club from the town of Pestszentlőrinc, Budapest. ==History== Szentlőrinci Atlétikai Club debuted in the 1957–58 season of the Hungarian League and finished third. == Name Changes == *1908–1919: Pestszentlőrinci Athletikai Club *1919–1945: Szentlőrinci Atlétikai Club *1945–1947: Szentlőrinci AC Barátság *1947: merger with Kőbányai Barátság *1947–1949: Szentlőrinci Atlétikai Club *1949: merger with Budapesti Postás SE *1956: reestablished *1957–1959: Petőfi Szentlőrinci Atlétikai Club ==Managers== * László Fenyvesi (1945–46) ==External links== * Profile ==References== Category:Football clubs in Hungary Category:1909 establishments in Hungary
title: Szentlőrinci AC
